FT  09 NOV 93 / PowerGen in heat and power deal
POWERGEN, the electricity generating company, has signed a combined heat and
power contract with Grovehurst Energy for the supply to three paper mills in
Kent.
PowerGen CHP, a subsidiary, will supply the demand for steam and electricity
for the paper mills in Kemsely and Sittingbourne. The plant will produce
80MW of electricity and 200MW of steam.
